news.title: Haryana government allocates plots under Mukhyamantri Gramin Awas Yojana 2.0
news.para: "The chief minister's vision is that no poor person in Haryana should remain without a roof. The government is continuously making efforts in this direction," an official statement said.

news.title: Odisha government launches survey to select beneficiaries under PM awas yojana
news.para: The survey will continue for about two months. It will include all the eligible families as per the promises made by Prime Minister Narendra Modi to provide 'pucca' houses to all, the minister said.

news.title: Landeed raises $5 million in Series X funding round
news.para: The Hyderabad-based startup stated that this round continues its earlier fundraising, which was among the largest seed rounds by a proptech startup in 2023.

news.title: UltraTech's open offer for India Cements oversubscribed
news.para: The ₹390-per-share offer, open from January 8 to 21, was subscribed 110%. It will increase UltraTech's stake in India Cements to 81.49%.The ₹390-per-share offer, open from January 8 to 21, was subscribed 110%.

news.title: SWAMIH Fund completes 50,000 homes since 2019
news.para: The fund set up in 2019 is managed by SBICAP Ventures Ltd, a State Bank Group company and it has no precedent or comparable peer fund in India or in the global markets.

news.title: ED to probe buyers of Dubai properties for forex violations and money laundering
news.para: The central agency has collated information gathered from its sources with the data received from the Income Tax (I-T) department and the Reserve Bank of India. A probe has begun, official sources told ET.

news.title: National Payments Corp of India leases 1.15 lakh sq ft office in Mumbai’s Goregaon
news.para: The lease includes a clause to escalate rentals by 15%, which will take effect after three years, taking the total rental payout to over Rs 136 crore over the entire tenure of the lease.

news.title: Mitsubishi Estate invests Rs 560 crore in Birla Estates' project in Bengaluru
news.para: Under the partnership, Birla Estates and MJR Investment Pte. (MIPL), an affiliate of MEC will share 51:49 economic interest respectively in the SPV.

news.title: DLF's net profit increases by 61.46% in Q3 FY25
news.para: DLF's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,737.47 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 5.72 per cent from Rs 1,643.51 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Mindspace REIT's reports a dip of 1.32% in its net profit in Q3 FY25
news.para: Mindspace Business Parks REIT clocked net operating income (NOI) growth of 8.3% year-on-year in Q3 FY25 to Rs 5,218 million. The board declared distribution of Rs 5.32 per unit aggregating to Rs 3,154.86 million.

news.title: Average flat sizes rose by 8% annually across seven cities in 2024: Report
news.para: The six-yearly trend of average flat sizes in the seven cities shows an overall 34% rise – from 1,145 sq ft in 2019 to 1,540 sq ft in 2024. In the last one year, there has been a 8% jump, with Hyderabad the only city to see flat sizes decrease in this period.

news.title: Retail leasing hits 6.4 million sq ft across eight cities in 2024: Report
news.para: The country added just 1.2 million sq ft of new retail space last year, but 2025 is expected to see a sharp rise in supply, with 5-6 million sq ft of grade A malls set to open in cities such as Delhi-NCR, Bengaluru, Hyderabad, and Mumbai.

news.title: New home construction in Ireland drops 6.7% to 30,000 in 2024
news.para: House completions recovered to a 15-year high of 32,500 in 2023, though that was still far below the level analysts say is needed to meet demand.

news.title: Orient Cement's net profit dips 77.46% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Orient Cement's net total income stood at Rs 645.86 crore in Q3 FY25, a dip of 14.25 per cent from Rs 753.22 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: SC forms SIT to probe Noida authority's alleged irregularities in land compensation
news.para: While instances of farmers not being paid adequate compensation for land acquired by the Authority were known, it now transpires there were as many as 20 instances where complaints were lodged about payment of excess compensation to some.

news.title: Build Capital plans to invest Rs 400 crore in Mumbai region in 2025
news.para: Build Capital is targeting to invest close to Rs 150 crore in Navi Mumbai. It has made its maiden investment in Satyam Group’s project.

news.title: Kochi: GCDA seeks amendments to land pooling rules for Infopark phase III
news.para: The govt has decided to implement the project using the land pooling method, with GCDA designated as the agency to oversee the process.

news.title: MMRDA signs MoUs worth $40 billion in WEF to transform Mumbai's infra
news.para: The investments focus on urban transport, regional development and advanced technologies, promising economic growth and improved living standards in the next 3-5 years.

news.title: Arkade Developers' net profit up 2.48% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Arkade Developers' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 231.40 crore in Q3 FY25, a dip of 3.38 per cent from Rs 239.49 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body recovers Rs 120 crore worth properties
news.para: The recovered property, spread over 2 acres and 16 guntas, was under illegal occupation for more than two decades.
